frigates and destroyers from seven nato 
countries have begun exercises in the mediterranean 
ships from italy germany portugal spain turkey britain and 
the united states are taking part in the 51day naval and air 
exercises dubbed deterrent force 290 which began friday 
the maneuvers by the western military alliance are held twice a 
year in the central and western mediterranean 
adm jonathan howe commander of natos southern forces said 
the exercises have a special relevance in the wake of the persian 
gulf crisis 
although this period of historic transformation in europe 
offers great hope for our future security the iraq invasion of 
kuwait has reminded us again that dangers remain along our 
borders he was quoted as saying in a nato press release 
it is most appropriate that we demonstrate natos 
continuing vigilance readiness and unity howe said 
