<TEXT>
the 265th quartermaster detachment of the south 
carolina national guard is one of the reserve units called up for 
duty in saudi arabia national writer fred bayles is with the 14 
guardsmen as they deploy overseas 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
after two weeks of hard training comes 
the hardest day 
its all right hon its going to be fine sgt earnest 
deloach said over and over as his wife lillie sobbed into his big 
chest its okay 
the 265th quartermaster detachment was leaving for the mideast 
ima jean rooker went to hug her son spc mark rooker a big 
strapping boy of 20 whose desert camouflage uniform was hung with 
canteens chemical warfare gear and his m16 
her smile dissolved into tears as she reached out for her 
youngest ooh was all she managed to say 
rookers father jerry stood to the side reaching in around 
his sunglasses to rub his eyes 
nineteen days ago rooker was a college student deloach was a 
prison supervisor and the rest of the 14man unit of the south 
carolina national guard worked jobs from truck driving to 
construction 
but military planners determined they needed water purification 
specialists in saudi arabia and the allendale sc unit showed up 
on someones list 
the unit was mobilized and rushed through a busy training 
schedule of physical conditioning marksmanship chemical warfare 
and radio communications 
now it was time for goodbyes 
it reminds me of your gi joe days mrs rooker said to her 
son her voice choking 
ill be home before you know it rooker said there was an 
uncomfortable silence 
suddenly spc ulysses calhoun began to sing sometimes i feel 
like a nut sometimes i dont 
everyone laughed and the tension was broken 
calhoun a 23yearold construction worker was usually the one 
to complain about the duty or the weather or the food today he was 
light and breezy joking with everyone and playing with his 
daughter whitney a fearless 3yearold who marched around with a 
us flag in her hand her fathers desertissue sunglasses propped 
on her face 
daddy why you always wearing the same clothes she asked 
pointing to his uniform 
whitney had seen her father on local television a number of 
times but calhoun was unimpressed with his celebrity 
id rather i was on a game show he said 
the goodbyes lingered through most of the day the unit traveled 
to hunter army air field in a tight little convoy of four pickup 
trucks and one van the families followed in their cars headlights 
on like a funeral procession 
no one talked in the crowded van why yall so quiet sgt 
john williams asked how about some music 
no one noticed the rap music booming out of the radio mostly 
they napped or stared out the window at signs and yellow ribbons 
wishing godspeed to troops already departed for saudi arabia 
the 265ths immediate destination was a large open airplane 
hangar halffilled with cots a color television bleachers video 
arcade games portable latrines and magazines in eastern airline 
folders creedence clearwater revival and pink floyd echoed from a 
loudspeaker in the rafter 
this was lockup a holding area for men and material 
shipping out to the mideast once in the men couldnt leave their 
families werent allowed near the area 
so the families gathered in bleachers set 1000 yards away to 
watch their husbands and sons load duffel bags and flak jackets 
onto one of their trucks 
a while later the families sent over packages of fried chicken 
and had their own picnic as the men ate in the sweltering heat of 
the runway 
but finally it was time for the families to go they shouted 
and waved as the men rushed out to wave back 
goodbye goodbye they called their voices high and thin in 
the distance 
