nuclear testing by 1995 in return for a commitment by the united 
states britain and the soviet union to begin negotiations on a 
ban conference sources said 
the compromise collapsed when western countries wanted to insert 
a reference to stepbystep negotiations mexico apparently saw 
the phrase as an attempt to water down the pledge by the nuclear 
powers said the sources speaking on condition of anomyity 
us policy states testing is needed to ensure the safety and 
reliability of nuclear weapon stockpiles us officials also note 
two of the worlds five nuclear weapon powers france and china 
are not members of the treaty organization 
the treaty binds states that do not possess nuclear weapons from 
building or acquiring them in return the three nuclear weapon 
states in the pact the united states britain and the soviet 
union pledge to work toward nuclear disarmament and to provide 
nonmilitary atomic technology to other nations 
the fourweek meeting attended by about 100 of the the groups 
141 member countries ended early saturday after unsuccessful 
negotiations between mexico the united states and other nations 
