emergency and said he would ditch in the north atlantic 
officials are fairly confident that what the captain sighted 
was a portion of the 727 said rescue worker ross brown 
the trawler captain spotted an object 65 feet to 82 feet long 
that was dark gray with red and white stripes matching air malta 
colors brown said 
the plane owned by faucett airlines of peru was leased by air 
malta and was carrying airline employees and their families 
the soviet captain made his sightings friday about 236 miles 
southeast of cape race newfoundland rescue officials said 
however brown said searchers had not spotted the object nor 
had anything else been recovered that was known to have come from 
the jet 
rescue officials didnt receive news of the sighting until 
